<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910404-0035</DOCNO><DOCID>910404-0035.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing Brief:   Noted....</HL><DATE>04/04/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MEGA PLTZ WNEWS WPPGY</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>ADVERTISING, MARKETING, PUBLIC RELATIONS (ADV)MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS, PROMOTIONS, APPOINTMENTS (PER)</NS><RE>MISSOURI (MO)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)VIRGINIA (VA)</RE><LP>   PUBLISHING: Media General Inc. sold its CliggottPublishing Co. to the unit's management. Terms weren'tdisclosed. The newspaper, broadcasting and cable televisioncompany said the sale reflects its restructuring toconcentrate on core communications businesses. Cliggottpublishes four monthly medical journals.                                                                                                       </LP><TEXT>   NEWSPAPERS: Pulitzer Publishing Co. said it will doublethe newsstand price of its daily St. Louis Post-Dispatchnewspaper, beginning April 15, to 50 cents. The price ofSunday newsstand copies also will increase 25 cents, to$1.25. Home subscription prices won't change.                                                                                                          WHO'S NEWS: Richard Torrenzano, the New York StockExchange's chief spokesman, was named executive vicepresident and assistant to the chief executive officer ofHill andamp; Knowlton Inc., a public relations unit of WPP GroupPLC. He was senior vice president, communications, at the BigBoard, which hasn't named a successor.</TEXT></DOC>